	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="whatIs">What is Story Sense?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>Story Sense is a web application where children can test their vocabulary and add knowledge to Story Sense by filling out blanks in a given 
story.</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="creators">Who created Story Sense?</p></h4>
	<br/><p> </p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="typesUsers">What are the different types of users?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>There are two kinds of users in Story Sense. They are the learners, and the reviewers.</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="learners">What are learners?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>Learners are creative and imaginative people that create 
	stories which other learners may view and like. Stories made by the learners are rated by the reviewers. In short, YOU are a learner!</p>
	
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="reviewers">What are reviewers?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>These are adult users who read the stories and answers entered by the learners. They give a score to the learner based on their stories. They may be your family members, teachers, or even old people.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="createStories">How can I create stories?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>In the top bar, there is a "Create Stories" button. Click it and you will be able to create your stories by inputting a title and filling up the blanks!
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="seeStories">How can I see my stories?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>In the top bar, there is a "My Stories" button. Click it to see your created stories, its score, and the number of people who liked that story. Create more stories to populate your "My Stories"!
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="createInaDay">How many stories can I create in a day?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>There is no limit to the number of stories you can create in a day, however, make sure that your created stories are good so that you can qualify for the leaderboards!
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="leaderboards">How can I get to the leaderboards?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>Everyone has the potential to get to the leaderboards. But, it will take effort and hard work to achieve that goal. To get to the leaderboards, you must have lots and lots of points and have high scores in your stories. Leaderboards are updated daily.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="SOTW">How can I get to the "Story of the Week"?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>To get to the "Story of the Week", your story must have the highest like for the week. The count starts from Monday and ends on Sunday.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="TOTW">How does a word qualify for the "Term of the Week"?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>A word qualifies for the "Term of the Week" if it is used frequently by a number of users.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="LevelUp">How can I level up?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>You can level up by scoring points from created stories. Scores are higher if the difficulty for the story is high. Create stories and aim to score high to be on the top!
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="ViewProfile">How can I view my profile?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>In the top bar, click on the "Profile". Once clicked, a list about your basic information, acquired badges, and statistics will be shown.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="ChangePass">How can I change my password?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>In the top bar, click on the "Profile" and click on the 'edit' button. Enter your old password and your new password. Select easy-to-remember passwords like Optimus12 or Batman45 so that you wouldn't forget.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="GetBadges">What are badges? How can I get more badges?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>Badges are proofs that you get a certain achievement. Requirements for the badges are shown by clicking the "Profile" in the top bar. If an achievement is achieved, the badge will color up. Black and White badges means that you did not get the requirement yet. Collect more badges to show off to your other friends!
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="Statistics">What are statistics?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>Statistics show the cool things that you are doing here. Like the number of stories you have made, highest score of a story and the story with the most number of likes.
	</p>
	</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td>
	<h4 id="h4Style"><p id="otherStories">Where can I see other people's stories?</p></h4>
	<br/><p>In the top bar, click the "Home". Once clicked, in the middle, there is a box called "Story Feed". Here, other learners stories are shown. You can read their stories and if you like the story, click on the "Like" button to show your appreciation!
	</p>
	</td>
